Writing different texts (description, short story, letters, essay, poems). Text organisation. Commonly misspelt words. Punctuation. Analysing and practising different writing tasks which are suitable for basic school students.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to teach students to write and analyse different texts as well as enlarge their vocabulary and develop stylistic skills. To give students ideas how to use different  writing activities in English lessons at basic school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course a student will know the main features of different texts (description, a short story, essay, report); analyse the style and vocabulary of dig'fferent texts and pay attention to their specific features;  creates different texts, using appropriate vocabulary and style; be able to teach the writing of different texts to primary school children; know the main rules of punctuation and use them correctly; know the spelling of difficult words and be able to correct them; analyse tasks written by their peers.
